<subSubSection id="C320B6A37A554A7CFF66FD5BD81FF9A7" pageId="8" pageNumber="1054" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B85E5287A554A7CFF66FD5BD81FF9A7" blockId="8.[126,765,178,1695]" pageId="8" pageNumber="1054">
Observations/Discussion: 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A9EAB7A554A7CFE76FD5BD853FD4C" baseAuthorityName="Latin" box="[398,624,667,687]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="8" pageNumber="1054" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="sancti-felicis">Cortinarius sancti-felicis</taxonomicName>
is recognised by the combination of an olivaceous grey pileus with a brownish alkaline reaction, the (brownish) velar scales, the strongly violaceous lamellae and large spores. It could be confused with atypical collections of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A9EAB7A554A7CFE58FCD5D86EFCCA" authorityName="in Quercus" box="[416,589,789,809]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="8" pageNumber="1054" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="parasuaveolens">C. parasuaveolens</taxonomicName>
lacking the blue colours on the pileus, and therefore showing a weaker alkaline reaction on the pileus than usual. We have found such collections of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A9EAB7A554A7CFF29FCB1DBC5FC66" authority="in Quercus" authorityName="in Quercus" box="[209,486,881,901]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="8" pageNumber="1054" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="parasuaveolens">C. parasuaveolens in Quercus</taxonomicName>
pubescens forests in central Europe, but they had a thin violaceous line just below the pileipellis in section, not seen in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A9EAB7A554A7CFE4BFC6ED861FC21" baseAuthorityName="Latin" box="[435,578,942,962]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="8" pageNumber="1054" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="sancti-felicis">C. sancti-felicis</taxonomicName>
, greyish lamellae with only a weak violaceous tinge on the edge, and smaller spores. Generally the violaceous colours of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A9EAB7A554A7CFD90FC2BD8DFFC1C" baseAuthorityName="Latin" box="[616,764,1003,1023]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="8" pageNumber="1054" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="sancti-felicis">C. sancti-felicis</taxonomicName>
(both stipe and lamellae) are more reddish violet than those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A9EAB7A554A7CFF6FFBE8DB1CFBDF" authorityName="in Quercus" box="[151,319,1064,1084]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="8" pageNumber="1054" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="parasuaveolens">C. parasuaveolens</taxonomicName>
. Two more species known to us (i.e. 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A9EAB7A554A7CFD57FBE8DAECFBB8" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="8" pageNumber="1054" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="insignibulbus">C. insignibulbus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A9EAB7A554A7CFEF1FB87DBA5FBB8" authorityName="Frøslev &amp; Jeppesen &amp; Laessøe" authorityYear="2006" box="[265,390,1095,1115]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="8" pageNumber="1054" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="selandicus">C. selandicus</taxonomicName>
) have the combination of a strong pink alkaline reaction on the bulbipellis and a negative (to brownish) reaction on the pileipellis. 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A9EAB7A554A7CFE03FB44D8B1FB7B" box="[507,658,1156,1176]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="8" pageNumber="1054" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="insignibulbus">C. insignibulbus</taxonomicName>
is smaller with a paler pileus. 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A9EAB7A554A7CFEB1FB62DBE0FB55" authorityName="Frøslev &amp; Jeppesen &amp; Laessøe" authorityYear="2006" box="[329,451,1186,1206]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="8" pageNumber="1054" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="selandicus">C. selandicus</taxonomicName>
has a paler pileus, sometimes with pale to violaceous veil patches (not small scales), paler lamellae, and so far it has only been recorded from nemoral Fagus sylvatica forests. These two species and 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A9EAB7A554A7CFDD9FB3ED8EDFAF1" authorityName="in Quercus" box="[545,718,1278,1298]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="8" pageNumber="1054" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="parasuaveolens">C. parasuaveolens</taxonomicName>
furthermore have smaller spores than 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A9EAB7A554A7CFE0FFADDD8A5FAD2" baseAuthorityName="Latin" box="[503,646,1309,1329]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="8" pageNumber="1054" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="sancti-felicis">C. sancti-felicis</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="1301F9AD7A554A7CFD6CFADDD8F4FAD2" box="[660,727,1309,1329]" captionStart="Fig 3" captionStartId="4.[126,158,1702,1722]" captionTargetBox="[130,759,245,1668]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[128,761,243,1670]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig 3 – Spore scatter diagrams with each point representing average spore size of single collections. (A) Cortinarius albertii and C. catharinae (B) C. calochrous, C. catharinae, C. chailluzii, C. cisticola and C. sublilacinopes. (C) C. vesterholtii, C. insignibulbus, C. nymphicolor, C. parasuaveolens, C. sanctifelicis and C. selandicus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366478/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="1054">Fig 3C</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A9EAB7A554A7CFD10FADDDAC6FAAC" authorityName="Frøslev &amp; Jeppesen &amp; Laessøe" authorityYear="2006" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="8" pageNumber="1054" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="vesterholtii">C. vesterholtii</taxonomicName>
has a brownish pileus, somewhat similar to mature fruit bodies of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A9EAB7A554A7CFEEDFA9ADB83FA8D" baseAuthorityName="Latin" box="[277,416,1370,1390]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="8" pageNumber="1054" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="sancti-felicis">C. sancti-felicis</taxonomicName>
, but has a negative alkaline reaction on the bulbipellis. 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A9EAB7A554A7CFE90FAB8DBD7FA6F" baseAuthorityName="Latin" box="[360,500,1400,1420]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="8" pageNumber="1054" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="sancti-felicis">C. sancti-felicis</taxonomicName>
is named after the abbey, L’Abbaye Saint Félix de Montceau, situated at the summit of the mountain range, Massif de la Gardiole in Hérault, 
<collectingCountry id="F32DA5B87A554A7CFD49FA75D8DAFA2A" box="[689,761,1461,1481]" name="France" pageId="8" pageNumber="1054">France</collectingCountry>
, where the type was collected. The species was included in the study of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAB98D97A554A7CFEFAFA32DBE7F9E5" author="Froslev TG &amp; Matheny PB &amp; Hibbett D" box="[258,452,1522,1542]" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution" pageId="8" pageNumber="1054" pagination="602 - 618" part="37" refId="ref13830" refString="Froslev TG, Matheny PB, Hibbett D, 2005. Lower level relationships in the mushroom genus Cortinarius (Basidiomycota, Agaricales): A comparison of RPB 1, RPB 2, and ITS phylogenies. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 37: 602 - 618." title="Lower level relationships in the mushroom genus Cortinarius (Basidiomycota, Agaricales): A comparison of RPB 1, RPB 2, and ITS phylogenies" type="journal article" year="2005">Frøslev et al. (2005)</bibRefCitation>
as C. cf. calochrous 1 (
<collectionCode id="ED2B7DED7A554A7CFD5BFA32D8EBF9E5" box="[675,712,1522,1542]" pageId="8" pageNumber="1054">TSJ</collectionCode>
2002- 072). An ITS sequence from the 
<typeStatus id="54815B8A7A554A7CFE2CF9D1D80DF9C6" box="[468,558,1553,1573]" pageId="8" pageNumber="1054">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A9EAB7A554A7CFDABF9D1D8C1F9C6" baseAuthorityName="Latin" box="[595,738,1553,1573]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="8" pageNumber="1054" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="sancti-felicis">C. sancti-felicis</taxonomicName>
is available at GenBank (accession 
<accessionNumber id="946978CB7A554A7CFE33F9F0D813F9A7" box="[459,560,1584,1604]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/DQ083776" pageId="8" pageNumber="1054">
<collectionCode id="ED2B7DED7A554A7CFE33F9F0DBCAF9A7" box="[459,489,1584,1604]" pageId="8" pageNumber="1054">DQ</collectionCode>
083776
</accessionNumber>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
